RINDERPEST - RUSSIA (AMUR) (03)
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Rinderpest - Russia (Amur) 980829213704
Rinderpest - Russia (Amur) (02) 980901233250

Date: Fri, 11 Sep 1998 11:13:40 -0400
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: BBC, ex Estonian radio and Turan Agency, 7 Sep 1998

Both Estonia and Azerbaijan have imposed [a ban on temporary imports of
Russian meat, hides, milk and dairy products following an outbreak of
cattle disease, described as "viral" and "cattle plague", indicating
rinderpest.
According to the reports, the outbreak is in the Amur region of Russia. In
Azerbaijan, all agencies and enterprises have been warned to obtain import
licenses from the State Veterinary Committee before proceeding on purchase
contracts.
--
